+1 Spun this up in dev and it worked like a charm.  Thanks for the fix.

@sardell mentioned that this is covered in the e2e tests, which is how he discovered the problem.  

This regression was caused by #1049, but since the e2e are not running reliably we probably did not attempt to run those before merging that one in.  Once we get #1004 merged, we should hopefully avoid regressions like this.
